# Visual Explainer

Generate self-contained HTML files for technical diagrams, visualizations, and data tables. Always open the result in the browser. Never fall back to ASCII art when this rule is active.

**Proactive table rendering.** When presenting tabular data (comparisons, audits, feature matrices, status reports), generate an HTML page instead of ASCII tables. Threshold: 4+ rows or 3+ columns → HTML page.

## Workflow

### 1. Think

Before writing HTML, commit to a direction:

**Constrained aesthetics (prefer these):**
- Blueprint — technical drawing feel, subtle grid background, deep slate/blue palette, monospace labels
- Editorial — serif headlines (Instrument Serif, Crimson Pro), generous whitespace, muted earth tones or deep navy + gold
- Paper/ink — warm cream `#faf7f5` background, terracotta/sage accents, informal feel
- Monochrome terminal — green/amber on near-black, monospace everything

**Flexible aesthetics (use with caution):**
- IDE-inspired — use a real named color scheme: Dracula, Nord, Catppuccin, Solarized, Gruvbox, One Dark, Rosé Pine
- Data-dense — small type, tight spacing, maximum information, muted colors

**Forbidden:**
- Neon dashboard (cyan + magenta + purple on dark)
- Gradient mesh (pink/purple/cyan blobs)
- Inter font + violet/indigo accents + gradient text

### 2. Structure

**Rendering approach by content type:**

| Content type | Approach |
|---|---|
| Architecture (text-heavy) | CSS Grid cards + flow arrows |
| Architecture (topology) | Mermaid |
| Flowchart / pipeline | Mermaid |
| Sequence diagram | Mermaid |
| Data table | HTML `<table>` |
| Timeline | CSS (central line + cards) |
| Dashboard | CSS Grid + Chart.js |

### 3. Build

- Single self-contained HTML file, no external dependencies except CDN libs
- Use Google Fonts CDN for typography
- Include light/dark theme toggle
- All CSS inline in `<style>`, all JS inline in `<script>`
- Responsive: works on mobile and desktop
- For Mermaid diagrams: load from CDN, use `securityLevel: 'loose'`

### 4. Verify

Before saving, check:
- File renders in browser without errors
- All interactive elements work (theme toggle, nav, tooltips)
- Text is readable at default zoom
- Mobile layout doesn't overflow

### Output

Write files to `~/.agent/diagrams/filename.html` and open in browser.

